# {{lb|en|medicine|nursing}} An [[ulcer]] caused by prolonged [[pressure]] on the skin as a person lies in a bed or sits in a chair or wheelchair; preventable with sufficient nursing care. 

====Synonyms====
* {{l|en|bedsore}}
* {{l|en|decubitus}}
* {{l|en|decubitus ulcer}}
* {{l|en|pressure sore}}

====Usage notes====
In current medical terminology preferred by professional societies devoted to nursing and to pressure ulcer prevention and care, the term {{m|en|pressure ulcer}} is preferred over its older synonyms. A multisociety international guideline on pressure ulcer prevention and care is periodically updated. 

